Edwina Booth https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edwina_Booth 0 Edwina Booth (September 13, 1904 – May 18, 1991) was an American actress. She is best known for the 1931 film Trader Horn, during the filming of which she contracted an illness which effectively ended her movie career.
